  areaText: 'Rogers Park (ZIP 60626) sits at the northern tip of Chicago, bordering Evanston and anchored by Loyola University Chicago along Sheridan Road. It is one of the city\'s most diverse neighborhoods, with a housing stock that ranges from single-family homes and bungalows inland to vintage three-flats and larger apartment buildings along the lakefront blocks. Flat roofs are common on the denser multi-unit buildings throughout the neighborhood; pitched asphalt shingle roofs predominate on bungalows and single-family homes west of Glenwood and Clark. Proximity to Lake Michigan on the eastern edge of Rogers Park creates meaningful wind and moisture exposure — high-wind-rated materials are especially important on buildings within two blocks of the lakefront. Many flat roofs in Rogers Park have EPDM or modified bitumen systems installed in the late 1990s to early 2000s that are now well past their useful life. Replacement costs typically run $8,000 to $16,000 for residential projects depending on building type, system, and square footage.',
  areaTextEs: 'Rogers Park (ZIP 60626) en el extremo norte de Chicago limita con Evanston y tiene la Universidad Loyola Chicago en Sheridan Road. La vivienda va desde casas unifamiliares y bungalows tierra adentro hasta three-flats vintage y edificios de apartamentos más grandes a lo largo del lago. Los costos de reemplazo oscilan entre $8,000 y $16,000.',
