  metaDescription: 'Roof replacement in Avondale, Chicago. Bungalow and two-flat specialists, licensed Illinois contractors, free estimates, written warranties.',
  intro: 'Avondale homeowners trust our verified contractors for full roof replacement. Bungalows, two-flats, and older single-family homes throughout this Northwest Side neighborhood — from Belmont to Addison along Pulaski and Kedzie — all need periodic full replacement.',
  introEs: 'Los propietarios de Avondale confían en nuestros contratistas para el reemplazo completo de techo. Bungalows, two-flats y casas más antiguas en este barrio del noroeste entre Belmont y Addison.',
  areaText: 'Avondale (ZIP 60618, 60641) sits on the Northwest Side between Logan Square to the east and Portage Park to the west, centered on the Belmont and Pulaski commercial corridors. The neighborhood has a dense mix of Chicago bungalows, brick two-flats, and some larger apartment buildings, mostly built between the 1920s and 1940s. Many homes are now on their second roofing cycle — 1990s-era replacements reaching end of life. The residential streets off the main corridors — Roscoe, School, Newport, Waveland — are lined with bungalows that have simple gable roofs and standard asphalt shingle systems. Two-flats throughout the neighborhood typically have flat EPDM or modified bitumen roofs. Avondale has a significant Latino community, and several contractors on our list have Spanish-speaking staff. Rising property values near the Logan Square border are motivating more owners to invest in quality replacements. Typical costs run $8,000 to $13,000 for bungalows and $8,000 to $14,000 for two-flat flat roofs.',
  areaTextEs: 'Avondale (ZIP 60618, 60641) está en el noroeste entre Logan Square y Portage Park, centrado en los corredores de Belmont y Pulaski. La mezcla de bungalows, two-flats y edificios más grandes, construidos entre los años 1920 y 1940. Muchas casas están en su segundo ciclo de techado. Los costos oscilan entre $8,000 y $13,000.',
  faq: [
    { q: 'How much does roof replacement cost in Avondale in 2026?', a: 'Full asphalt shingle replacement on a typical Avondale bungalow runs $8,000 to $13,000. Two-flat flat roof replacement costs $8,000 to $14,000 for a TPO or EPDM system. Bungalows with two existing shingle layers — common on Avondale homes over 30 years old — require full tear-off per Illinois code, adding $1,000 to $1,500. Free on-site estimates from all six listed contractors.' },
    { q: 'My Avondale bungalow has two layers of shingles. What does that mean for replacement?', a: 'Illinois building code prohibits adding a third shingle layer, so full tear-off of both existing layers is required before new shingles can be installed. This adds $1,000 to $1,500 to the project. The benefit of full tear-off: your contractor can inspect the original board sheathing or plywood decking for rot, soft spots, or deterioration. Any damaged boards are replaced at $80 to $120 per sheet before new shingles go on. Your contractor confirms layer count and decking condition during the free assessment.' },
    { q: 'Are there Spanish-speaking roofing contractors serving Avondale?', a: 'Yes. Several contractors on our list have Spanish-speaking staff and can handle the full process — estimate, contract, and on-site communication — in Spanish. Avondale has a substantial Latino community and bilingual service is frequently requested in this neighborhood. Confirm Spanish availability when you call for your free estimate.' },
    { q: 'What flat roof system is best for an Avondale two-flat?', a: 'TPO membrane is the recommended choice for new flat roof installations on Avondale two-flats. TPO outperforms EPDM in Chicago\'s freeze-thaw climate with heat-welded seams that resist winter membrane separation, reflects summer heat reducing upper-unit cooling costs, and has a longer lifespan of 25 to 35 years versus EPDM\'s 15 to 25. For a typical Avondale two-flat, TPO replacement costs $8,000 to $14,000 depending on square footage.' },
    { q: 'How do I know if my Avondale bungalow roof needs replacement vs repair?', a: 'Replace rather than repair when: the roof is 20+ years old, you see consistent granule deposits in gutters after rain, interior ceiling stains appear in early spring after ice dams melt, or you have had two or more repair calls in five years. The 25% rule also applies: if your repair estimate exceeds 25 to 30% of what full replacement would cost, replacement is the financially correct decision. A free inspection from any listed contractor gives you a definitive answer without commitment.' },
    { q: 'Is a permit required for roof replacement in Avondale?', a: 'Yes. The City of Chicago requires a building permit for all full roof replacements in Avondale. All listed contractors pull this permit as part of every project at no extra charge. Never work with a contractor who suggests skipping the permit — this creates code violations that appear during home sales and can void homeowner insurance coverage. Verify any contractor\'s Illinois IDFPR license at idfpr.com before signing.' },
  ],
