  metaDescription: 'Roof replacement in Cicero, IL near Chicago. Spanish-speaking contractors available, all roof types, licensed Illinois contractors, free estimates.',
  intro: 'Cicero homeowners trust our verified contractors for full roof replacement. Spanish-speaking staff available. This large suburb directly west of Chicago has extensive bungalow and two-flat housing stock — and its own permit requirements our contractors know well.',
  introEs: 'Los propietarios de Cicero confían en nuestros contratistas para el reemplazo completo de techo. Personal de habla hispana disponible. Este gran suburbio al oeste de Chicago tiene extensas viviendas de bungalows y two-flats con requisitos de permiso propios.',
  areaText: 'Cicero (ZIP 60804) is a large independent suburb directly west of Chicago, sharing its eastern border with the Austin neighborhood. With roughly 85,000 residents, Cicero is one of Illinois\'s largest municipalities. The town has a predominantly Mexican-American community and a housing stock that closely mirrors Chicago\'s West Side — rows of Chicago-style bungalows and brick two-flats built between the 1920s and 1940s along 25th, 26th, and Cermak Road. Cicero has its own town government and building permit system separate from Chicago. Several contractors on our list have Spanish-speaking staff and extensive experience completing roofing projects under Cicero\'s permit and inspection process. Typical costs run $8,000 to $14,000 for bungalows and two-flat flat roofs.',
  areaTextEs: 'Cicero (ZIP 60804) es un gran suburbio independiente directamente al oeste de Chicago con aproximadamente 85,000 residentes. Tiene una comunidad predominantemente mexicano-americana y viviendas tipo West Side de Chicago — bungalows y two-flats construidos entre los años 1920 y 1940. Los costos oscilan entre $8,000 y $14,000.',
  faq: [
    { q: 'Are there Spanish-speaking roofing contractors serving Cicero?', a: 'Yes. Several contractors on our list have Spanish-speaking staff and can handle the full project — estimate, contract review, permit coordination, and on-site communication — in Spanish. Cicero\'s predominantly Mexican-American community makes bilingual roofing service consistently in demand. Confirm Spanish availability when you call for your free estimate.' },
    { q: 'How much does roof replacement cost in Cicero in 2026?', a: 'Full asphalt shingle replacement on a typical Cicero bungalow runs $8,000 to $13,000. Two-flat flat roof replacement costs $8,000 to $14,000 for a TPO or EPDM system. Bungalows with two existing shingle layers require full tear-off per Illinois code, adding $1,000 to $1,500. Free estimates from all six listed contractors — estimates include Cicero\'s permit fees in the total scope.' },
    { q: 'Does Cicero have different permit requirements than Chicago for roof replacement?', a: 'Yes. Cicero has its own town building permit system entirely separate from the City of Chicago. The Cicero Town Hall issues building permits and requires town inspection after completion. All listed contractors serving Cicero are experienced with Cicero\'s permit process and include permit coordination in the project scope. Never work with a contractor who skips Cicero\'s permit — this creates title issues and code violations.' },
    { q: 'What roofing materials work best for Cicero\'s Chicago-style bungalows?', a: 'Architectural asphalt shingles with a 30-year manufacturer warranty and 130 mph wind rating are the recommended standard for Cicero bungalows — the same specification that performs well on Chicago\'s West Side bungalows. Class 4 impact-resistant shingles cost 10 to 15 percent more but may qualify for 20 to 30 percent insurance premium discounts from Illinois insurers.' },
    { q: 'My Cicero bungalow was built in the 1930s and still has the original sheathing. What should I know?', a: 'Older Cicero bungalows with original 1920s to 1930s board sheathing may have individual boards that have rotted or deteriorated over 80 to 90 years. These are identified and replaced during the tear-off phase at $80 to $120 per board. It is common to replace 5 to 20 percent of the decking on a bungalow of this age — your contractor documents all deteriorated boards and includes replacement costs in the written estimate.' },
    { q: 'How do I verify a Cicero roofing contractor is properly licensed?', a: 'Verify the Illinois IDFPR roofing license at idfpr.com before signing any contract. Contractors working in Cicero must hold an active Illinois license — Cicero does not issue its own separate roofing contractor licenses. Also confirm General Liability insurance of at least $250,000 and Workers Compensation coverage. All six contractors on our list are pre-verified for active IDFPR licenses and required insurance.' },
  ],
  faqEs: [
    { q: '¿Hay contratistas de habla hispana que sirven Cicero?', a: 'Sí. Varios contratistas de nuestra lista tienen personal de habla hispana y pueden manejar todo el proyecto en español. La comunidad predominantemente mexicano-americana de Cicero hace que el servicio bilingüe sea muy solicitado.' },
    { q: '¿Cuánto cuesta el reemplazo de techo en Cicero en 2026?', a: 'El reemplazo completo de tejas en un bungalow típico de Cicero cuesta entre $8,000 y $13,000. El reemplazo de techo plano en un two-flat cuesta entre $8,000 y $14,000. Los estimados incluyen las tarifas de permiso de Cicero.' },
    { q: '¿Cicero tiene requisitos de permiso diferentes a los de Chicago?', a: 'Sí. Cicero tiene su propio sistema de permisos completamente separado de Chicago. El Ayuntamiento de Cicero emite permisos y requiere inspección después de la finalización.' },
    { q: '¿Qué materiales funcionan mejor para los bungalows de estilo Chicago en Cicero?', a: 'Las tejas de asfalto arquitectónicas con garantía de 30 años y 130 mph de viento son el estándar recomendado. Las tejas Clase 4 pueden calificar para descuentos de seguro del 20 al 30 por ciento.' },
    { q: 'Mi bungalow en Cicero fue construido en los años 30. ¿Qué debo saber?', a: 'Los bungalows más antiguos con entablado original de los años 1920 a 1930 pueden tener tablones que se han podrido. Estos se reemplazan durante la demolición a $80 a $120 por tablón.' },
    { q: '¿Cómo verifico que un contratista de Cicero tiene licencia correctamente?', a: 'Verifique la licencia IDFPR de Illinois en idfpr.com. Los contratistas en Cicero deben tener una licencia activa de Illinois. Todos los contratistas de nuestra lista están preseleccionados.' },
  ],
