  areaText: 'Little Village (ZIP 60623), known as La Villita, is the commercial and cultural heart of Chicago\'s Mexican community on the Southwest Side, anchored by the 26th Street shopping corridor — one of the highest-grossing retail strips in Chicago. The neighborhood has a dense mix of bungalows, two-flats, three-flats, and commercial buildings. Most residential buildings were constructed between 1910 and 1940 and many are now on their second or third roof replacement cycle. Flat roofs dominate the two-flat and commercial stock; bungalows on streets like Millard, Trumbull, and Kedvale have pitched asphalt shingle roofs. Rising property values in Little Village have motivated many owners to invest in quality replacements rather than repeated patching. Several contractors on our list have Spanish-speaking staff and have completed extensive work in this community. Typical replacement costs run $8,000 to $14,000 for residential projects.',
