  areaText: 'Chatham (ZIP 60619, 60620) is a stable South Side neighborhood with a strong tradition of Black homeownership, stretching roughly from 75th to 87th Streets between the Dan Ryan Expressway and Cottage Grove Avenue. The housing stock is predominantly brick bungalows and two-flats built between the 1920s and 1950s — well-maintained properties on block after block of residential streets like Langley, St. Lawrence, and Wabash. Many Chatham homeowners are long-term residents who take pride in their properties and approach roof replacement as a planned, quality investment rather than an emergency repair. Asphalt architectural shingles with 30-year warranties are the standard replacement material. Many roofs from the 1990s are now reaching end of life. Typical replacement costs run $8,000 to $14,000 for a standard Chatham bungalow or brick single-family home.',
